trpzClientSessionTc.name: trpzClientSessionTc

revisions.description: v1.4.0: Introduced TCs: TrpzClientDeviceType, TrpzClientDeviceGroupName, TrpzClientDeviceProfileName. (for 8.0 release)
v1.3.3: Added User Access Type value 'profile' (5). Reserved User Access Type value 6. (for 7.5 release)
v1.1.0: Introduced TrpzClientAccessMode to be used instead of TrpzAccessType from trpzApTc module. (In 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified.)

TrpzUserAccessType.name: TrpzUserAccessType
TrpzUserAccessType.description: Enumeration of user access types (also referred to as ''login types'').

TrpzClientSessionState.name: TrpzClientSessionState
TrpzClientSessionState.description: Enumeration of the client session states. Value 'associated(1)' applies only to wireless sessions. Value 'wired(8)' applies only to wired sessions.

TrpzClientDot1xState.name: TrpzClientDot1xState
TrpzClientDot1xState.description: Enumeration of the dot1x states for a client.

TrpzClientAuthenProtocolType.name: TrpzClientAuthenProtocolType
TrpzClientAuthenProtocolType.description: Enumeration of the dot1x client authentication protocol types.

TrpzClientAccessMode.name: TrpzClientAccessMode
TrpzClientAccessMode.description: Describes the access mode (type) used by client. Value 'ap(2)' indicates a client that is attached to the switch via an access point. Value 'wired(3)' indicates a client that is attached to the switch via the wired network (no access point is involved).

TrpzClientDeviceType.name: TrpzClientDeviceType
TrpzClientDeviceType.description: The type of a client device. Consists of printable ASCII characters between 0x21 (!), and 0x7e (~), with no leading, embedded, or trailing space. Is a zero length string if unknown.

TrpzClientDeviceGroupName.name: TrpzClientDeviceGroupName
TrpzClientDeviceGroupName.description: The name of a group of device types. Consists of printable ASCII characters between 0x21 (!), and 0x7e (~), with no leading, embedded, or trailing space. Is a zero length string if unknown.

TrpzClientDeviceProfileName.name: TrpzClientDeviceProfileName
TrpzClientDeviceProfileName.description: The name of a device profile. A device profile is a collection of policies that apply to one or more types of client devices. Consists of printable ASCII characters between 0x21 (!) and 0x7e (~), with no leading, embedded, or trailing space. Is a zero length string if unknown.
